==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharyngognathi
<hw>Phar`yn*gog"na*thi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Pharynx</er>, and <er>Gnathic</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of fishes in which the lower
pharyngeal bones are united. It includes the scaroid, labroid, and
embioticoid fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharyngolaryngeal</ent>⟦br⟧
